<p>The Foundation has the opportunity toâGive it Twiceâ: The foundation gives their investment dona- tion to Chateaux du Monde, which leverages the funds for the designated charity/charities. At the dissolution of the partnership, Chateaux du Monde returns the foundationâs initial Investment, which can then be gifted again to the Foundationâs designated charity/charities.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="496e84c20cd29ede1" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-580-1" data-target="#496e84c20cd29ede1" href="#496e84c20cd29ede1"><span class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-fusion-box" aria-hidden="true"></i></span><span class="fusion-toggle-heading">What is a Donation Investment?</span></a></h4></div><div id="496e84c20cd29ede1" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix">
<p>This $5,000,000 was originally conceived of as a donation from the foundation to CDM to have CDM give the foundationâs charities auction lots of one week stays at the Charitable Estates, Our advisors suggested making this an investment in order to not create more compliance and work for a foundation; therefore this is an investment in real estate. (Please consult Private Placement Memorandum for details)</p>
</div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="0f277b8f0537edbbc" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-580-1" data-target="#0f277b8f0537edbbc" href="#0f277b8f0537edbbc"><span class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-fusion-box" aria-hidden="true"></i></span><span class="fusion-toggle-heading">How many destinations will ultimately be available for Investor use?</span></a></h4></div><div id="0f277b8f0537edbbc" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix">
<p>A total of twelve (12) Chateaux du Monde culturally authentic estate destinations are planned, beginning with Castiglion del Bosco, Tuscany, and expanding over the next five to seven years.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="908365a7874b3c7f2" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-580-1" data-target="#908365a7874b3c7f2" href="#908365a7874b3c7f2"><span class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-fusion-box" aria-hidden="true"></i></span><span class="fusion-toggle-heading">What is the average size of the estates?</span></a></h4></div><div id="908365a7874b3c7f2" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix">
<p>The minimum requirement is access to estates or island grounds of 100 acres or more. Several targeted estates and islands are up to 6,500 acres. Each of the twelve estate properties will have twelve foundation suites available.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="55c3dcc3d37257543" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-580-1" data-target="#55c3dcc3d37257543" href="#55c3dcc3d37257543"><span class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-fusion-box" aria-hidden="true"></i></span><span class="fusion-toggle-heading">How often can a Foundation use or offer the estate?</span></a></h4></div><div id="55c3dcc3d37257543" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix">
<p>Each Investor Foundation shall have 48 suite weeks (7 nights in each week) access each year (12 suites x 4 weeks = 48 suite weeks) for fundraising and/or charitable use. Reservations for all 48 weeks are pre-assigned 18 to 24 months prior to each reserved week. Each of the 48 weeks are divided into a package of 12 suites per week or 4 weeks a year. The reservation protocol is based on a quarterly rotation model with each of the 12 foundations alternating different weeks each quarter of every year. (Please see CDM âThe Plan for reservation protocols and details)</p>
</div></div></div><div class="fusion-panel panel-default"><div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title toggle"><a aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="a90c6073875cdb2cd" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-580-1" data-target="#a90c6073875cdb2cd" href="#a90c6073875cdb2cd"><span class="fusion-toggle-icon-wrapper" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-fusion-box" aria-hidden="true"></i></span><span class="fusion-toggle-heading">What is the Reservation Protocol?</span></a></h4></div><div id="a90c6073875cdb2cd" class="panel-collapse collapse "><div class="panel-body toggle-content fusion-clearfix">
<p>The reservation system is modeled after theâResidence Clubâmodel and uses an alternating priority based system. The first week (12 suites per week) is offered to each Foundation based on the date of their initial acceptance as an Investor. The selected week varies each quarter for 4 quarters each year, moving down the numeric list, and giving each foundation the first position each quarter. The second week of usage is then made available in the reverse order, with the last Foundationâs investment date going first in the selection process, and the order moving up the list each subse- quent quarter. The third usage week is taken from the middle order of the Foundationâs joining dates, and moving down each quarter in alternating fashion.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div><div class="fusion-clearfix"></div></div></div><div class="fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-21 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;"><div class="fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy" style="background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><div class="fusion-sep-clear"></div><div class="fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep" style="margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;"></div><div class="fusion-sep-clear"></div><div class="fusion-clearfix"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="contact"><div class="fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-6 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling" style="background-color: #4e2108;background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:30px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:30px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;" ><div class="fusion-builder-row fusion-row"><div class="fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-22 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:20px;"><div class="fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy" style="background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><div class="fusion-sep-clear"></div><div class="fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep" style="margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:20px;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;"></div><div class="fusion-sep-clear"></div